Guiding principles for the development of the EasyEA framework

1. Start with Real-World Needs
Build the framework based on actual challenges organizations face, not theoretical ideas.

2. Make It Easy to Learn
Ensure the framework can be understood and used by anyone.

3. Focus on Quick Wins
Design the framework to deliver results quickly

4. Provide Clear Guidance
Create simple, actionable steps for users to follow.

5. Prioritize Collaboration
Design the framework to encourage teamwork across departments and teams.

6. Keep It Lightweight
Avoid overloading the framework with unnecessary layers or complexity.

7. Test and Evolve
The framework improves over time based on feedback and results.

8. Encourage Experimentation
The framework is open to testing new ideas without fear of failure.

9. Focus on Outcomes, Not Outputs
Design the framework to prioritize achieving meaningful results rather than just producing documentation or models.

